entry.title: Revamp the Cronet telemetry manifest flag
entry.content:
Before:







After:











The rationale is as follows:



- The meta-data entries are moved to a "meta-data holder service" as application-level meta-data tends to cause scalability issues with PackageManager queries.



- The prefix is changed from "org.chromium.net" to "android.net.http" to make the names look less jarring when using Cronet in AOSP (i.e. HttpEngine). This means the AOSP prefix is also used even when using the Chromium variant of Cronet, but that seems more tolerable. We could also keep using the Chromium prefix in Chromium and adjust it downstream in AOSP, but that would add complexity for little benefit.



- The name "Cronet" is removed because that is redundant with the "android.net.http" prefix, and AOSP surfaces are not supposed to use the term "Cronet".



This change is safe from a backwards compatibility perspective because no apps use this flag today, except for one (AGSA), which has been adjusted to specify both the old and new meta-data entries so that it will behave correctly regardless of which Cronet version it's using.



We take the opportunity to also simplify the test code - we can simply replace the entire meta-data object instead of "patching" it because Cronet owns the entire Bundle.

entry.title: media/gpu: Add Tile4 support to VA-API WebP and JPEG Decoding Tests
entry.content:
Add some utilities to map Tile4 buffers in the VA-API WebP and JPEG

DMAbuf export unittests. Currently these tests assume that the exported

DMA buffer is mappable by importing into minigbm, but some newer

platforms use Tile4 formatted buffers that aren't directly mappable.

This patch works around the issue by forcibly mapping the buffers

linearly and then manually detiling the pixel data in a userspace

utility function.



Note that we opted not to expose this functionality directly through

minigbm, because we decided this should be a test-only path for the time

being.



Bug: b:284818781 b:281478339 b:272629079

Test: Tested by running VaapiJpegDecoderWithDmaBufsTest.DecodeSucceeds*

and VaapiWebPDecoderTest.DecodeAndExportAsNativePixmapDmaBuf* tests on a

Rex.

entry.title: Removed redundant check in renderer filling logic
entry.content:
ForEachMatchingFormFieldCommon stores the element that were filled in a

list matched_fields that it returns by the end of the function.



While iterating over the fields in `data` to find the corresponding

blink element and fill it, there's a heuristic check that breaks out of

the loop if matching_fields has the same size as the list of blink

elements.



Regardless of the fact that this check isn't really necessary, it is not

quite useful because during that loop only the initiating element is

added to the list and nothing else, which considerably narrows the scope

where this check is useful, which are single-field forms.



This CL removes this check for simplicity, and fixes tests that were

relying on it.

entry.title: Strength-reduce SVG pattern/gradient invalidation
entry.content:
None of the changes that cause InvalidPattern() or InvalidGradient()

to be called changes state that require a layout pass to update.

Split out a InvalidateCache() from InvalidateCacheAndMarkForLayout() to

be able to invalidate the cache without triggering layout, and then

use it in InvalidPattern() and InvalidGradient().



This should make said invalidations slightly cheaper (no layout pass)

and will allow performing invalidation of a pattern/gradient from within

layout (for example while handling a change in viewport dimensions).

entry.title: iwa: Implement update discovery
entry.content:
This CL implements the first of two parts of IWA updates: Update

discovery. The `IsolatedWebAppUpdateManager` runs a repeating timer as

long as an IWA is installed to regularly check for updates. Update

checks are performed serially, so that memory and network usage is

spread out over time.



The `IsolatedWebAppUpdateDiscoveryTask` is deliberately not implemented

as a `WebAppCommand`, because it might take some time to download a

potentially big Web Bundle over a slow internet connection. If the task

was blocking all other actions on the bundle, such as uninstallation,

the user experience would unnecessarily suffer.



Bug: 1444407

entry.title: Parameterize suggestion behavior for manual fallbacks
entry.content:
As outlined in the DD, the flow of triggering and selecting suggestions

is the following:

- Suggestions are triggered through an AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource,

like clicking into a field.

- Suggestions are generated and sent to the external delegate.

- Once the user interacts (accepts or previews) a suggestion, the

BrowserAutofillManager is notified with the appropriate

AutofillTriggerSource. The manager then asks the driver to fill the

relevant fields.



This CL adapts this flow for manual fallbacks:

- A new AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource and AutofillTriggerSource for

manual fallbacks is introduced.

- Logic is added to the external delegate that converts from the

suggestion trigger source to the trigger source. It contains a more

detailed comment on this distinction.

This suggestion trigger source is available to the external delegate

through the popup controller, as refactored in crrev.com/c/4595077.

- The filling/previewing logic in the manager is adapted, such that

autofilling operations from the manual fallback AutofillTriggerSource

take ac=unrecognized fields into consideration.



The follow-up crrev.com/c/4549478 uses this mechanism to add an entry

to the context menu, which triggers suggestions through the manual

fallback AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource.



Another follow-up CL will use the AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource to

modify the profile suggestion generation logic. Right now, when

generating the suggestion labels, only ac != unrecognized fields are

taken into account. independently of the suggestion trigger source.

entry.title: [execCommand] Fix `RebalanceWhitespaceOnTextSubstring`
entry.content:
This patch fixes `RebalanceWhitespaceOnTextSubstring` when

`white-space: pre-line`.



It checks `white-space: preserve` and returns early if so in

`CanRebalance`[1], then replace consecutive collapsible white

spaces, but it should not handle new lines as collapsible

white spaces when `white-space: pre-line`.



This CL matches the WebKit behavior at:

https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=252226



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/editing/commands/composite_edit_command.cc;l=703?q=CompositeEditCommand::CanRebalance&ss=chromium%2Fchromium%2Fsrc
